  "prompt": "I have got 986 rank in BHU UET test for BA social science, will I get admission in BA social?",
  "response": "With a rank of 986 in the BHU UET for BA Social Science, your chances of getting admission into BA Social Sciences at BHU are **decent, but not guaranteed**. Here's a breakdown of factors to consider and what you can expect:\n\n**Factors Influencing Your Admission:**\n\n*   **Category:** Your category (General, OBC, SC, ST, EWS) is a major factor. Cutoffs vary significantly between categories. If you belong to a reserved category, your chances are much higher than a general category candidate with the same rank.\n*   **Number of Seats:** The total number of seats available for BA Social Sciences at BHU. This number changes slightly each year, but generally, it's a significant number.\n*   **Cutoff Trends:** Previous years' cutoff trends for BA Social Science admission at BHU. This will give you a realistic idea of what ranks have been admitted in the past. Check official BHU admission websites and reliable educational portals for this data.\n*   **Student Preferences:** The choices of other candidates ranked higher than you. If many students with better ranks choose other courses or universities, your chances increase.\n*   **Number of Rounds of Counseling:** BHU conducts multiple rounds of counseling. Seats often become available in later rounds as students withdraw or choose other options.\n*   **BHU Affiliated Colleges:** Consider the affiliated colleges like Arya Mahila PG College (AMPGC), Vasant Kanya Mahavidyalaya (VKM), and Vasanta College for Women (VCW). Their cutoffs are generally lower than the main campus. If you're open to these colleges, your chances significantly improve.\n\n**General Expectations:**\n\n*   **General Category:** For the General category, a rank of 986 is borderline. Admission to the main campus will be difficult, but there's still a possibility in later rounds of counseling, especially if seats remain vacant. You have a better chance at affiliated colleges.\n*   **OBC Category:** Your chances are significantly better than General category, particularly for affiliated colleges and possibly the main campus in later rounds.\n*   **SC/ST Category:** You have a very good chance of getting admission, likely in the main campus itself.\n*   **EWS Category:** Your chances are good, similar to or slightly better than OBC.\n\n**What You Should Do:**\n\n1.  **Check Previous Year Cutoffs:** This is crucial. Look at the previous years' cutoff ranks for each category and each round of counseling for BA Social Science at BHU (both main campus and affiliated colleges). This will give you the most accurate estimate.\n2.  **Attend Counseling:** Attend all rounds of counseling. Even if you don't get a seat in the first round, attend subsequent rounds as seats become available.\n3.  **Keep Options Open:** Don't rely solely on BHU. Apply to other universities and courses as a backup.\n4.  **Be Prepared to Wait:** Admission processes can be lengthy and uncertain. Be patient and keep checking for updates on the BHU admission portal.\n5.  **Consider Affiliated Colleges:** Be open to joining the affiliated colleges if you don't get a seat on the main campus. You can always try to transfer to the main campus later (though transfers are not guaranteed).\n6.  **Verify Information:** Always rely on official BHU websites and notifications for the most up-to-date and accurate information. Avoid relying on unverified sources.\n\n**In summary, with a rank of 986, your chances of admission to BA Social Science at BHU are decent, but highly dependent on your category. Research previous year cutoffs, attend all counseling rounds, and keep your options open.** Good luck!\n",
